@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontColor #000000
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #000000
skinparam TitleFontColor #000000

title Postgres Provider Driver Loading (Before)

actor "Client/Edge Bundler" as Bundler
component "@xylex-group/athena\n(root entry)" as Root #E3F2FD
component "schema/index.ts\nbarrel export" as SchemaIndex #FFF3E0
component "schema/postgres-provider.ts" as Provider #FFEBEE
component "pg driver\n(node-postgres)" as PgDriver #FFCDD2

Bundler --> Root : import { createClient }
Root --> SchemaIndex : re-export chain
SchemaIndex --> Provider : static module link
Provider --> PgDriver : top-level import { Pool } from 'pg'
Bundler --> PgDriver : resolver touches Node-only dependency

note bottom of Provider
Even without calling introspection, loading the provider module
links pg immediately in the root bundle path.
end note
@enduml
